title: okinawa guest house
address: Q5F5+76G okinawa guest house, Yangon
user_reviews:
[{"Name":"Aung Hein Htun","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocLl3XFbx9728FSecb30p5ArHzkOOjrbQCQ6DylJUzF3zwDP4Q=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":1,"Description":"BAD SERVICE, talks down on customers, has terrible staff, and the room arent clean. I would not recommend whatsoever! PLEASE avoid this hotel at all cost!","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Exit H","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/local-reviews/AJMZ0QcHdm0oAuHtzPwzcwUtTqUfPbZXmYnyyN78cO7_Z2aHVLpBkIuu0olTbSpOuQZcPV9sYQ=s120-c-br100","Rating":0,"Description":"We have stayed there 7 times and it is always nice to return. Being one of the first bunch of guest houses before they popped up like mushrooms 2 years ago Okinawa is a lovely place. Rooms are basic but have a fan or A/C. The bathrooms could use a bit of a treat though and the wifi could be faster / working in all areas. Breakfast is included in the price, varies every day and is being served on the tables in front of the guest house so you can watch the atmosphere around 32nd street. Sule Pagoda is 2 mins walk.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Cello A","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/local-reviews/AJMZ0QeYuXGoFc9HnT35lAJ46cKDIsHY7nNIKUKz_f8yINNlqyrU48jCx-4ctPzihRKgde030w=s120-c-br100","Rating":0,"Description":"Good location, pretty close to the sule pagoda and chinatown, good breakfast and wifi but the staff is really confused and disoganized. I stayed in a shared room, when I come back to the hostel at night to sleep there was other people sleeping on my bed. My luggage was outside with all my belongings. The staff putted me in other room. I was really disappoitend. I could lost something!!! I got really angry but ok, I was in Burma. I suggest you to find other hostel to avoid this kind of thing.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Janny","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWGX7ehkqfn6ZmkKzjxNzdDb6dHNMdA7FEE_BbTDHinkcdLPt5dVg=s120-c-rp-mo-ba6-br100","Rating":3,"Description":"Located less than a 5 mins walk from Sule Pagoda, it's a small guesthouse located on a small street in a busy area.  Lots of vendors, and you can purchase your bus ticket on the same street.  I booked one bed in a 4 or 5 bed dorm.  The mattresses were on the floor with a mosquito net.  Even though there was AC, it was still very hot at night.  I attract mosquitos fairly easily, and woke up to more than 10 bites all over my body, even though there was a mosquito net.  The bathroom kept running out of toilet paper.  The only pros about this place is the location, as well as the breakfast.  Otherwise, you pay for what you get here, and bring toilet paper.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Diane B","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/local-reviews/AJMZ0Qczn4VDfUM6-AtEt-6oaNazFa-i9Fy6kqPVfGIlPil6vJulEYyK8t930jZwOW4hD80mzw=s120-c-br100","Rating":0,"Description":"One thing to be aware of is the mosquitoes. They acknowledge this issue by having mosquito nets for the bed but you have to do the work of making sure you are not bitten while you sleep. 1) shake the net off of sneaky mosquitoes--when we got there the net was hanging suspending from the bed and there were two mosquitos on the net and 2) once the mosquitoes are away from the bed, tuck the net under the bed so they don't get in. There was a single low lit light in the bathroom--had to use a flash light to see toilet, cold shower water and the sink water didn't work. The walls are paper thin and one guest kept banging on the door--lost his key or something. Good thing we only stayed there for an overnight and good thing we had our mosquito deterrent spray! If we stayed for longer the rating may be lower.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Matthew O'Keeffe","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjW6r-_DU84rALKi0a2Av9A2UbOkhdnP6bI8lxE3rvJKpeuHY7M_xg=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":1,"Description":"Ok, so there are apparently two Okinawa guest houses. Both within 100m of each other. Review for this is for guest house number one.

The guest house appears to be run by children. The person checking you in is a 16 year old boy who's English is just enough to check you in. That's all. I actually made a booking from Agoda and apparently they had no record of it. But still had a room available. So lucky? I guess. The door to the room is an old fashioned Key and lock system that doesn't work without jiggling the door and key for 5mins to try find the sweet spot.

The rooms have no hot water. Only cold. The power shuts off in the rain and you'll get a torch to use in the room.

The bed has bugs and you'll wake up with bite marks over you. The bed and mosquito net both had blood stains on them. I ended buying a bed sheet myself to use while staying here from the local shopping. Also no wifi at all.

This is honestly just a terrible place to attempt to stay. There are a lot better options for the money. The double room was 25,000 Myanmar money for one night. So around $20.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Caleb F","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/local-reviews/AJMZ0QeYuXGoFc9HnT35lAJ46cKDIsHY7nNIKUKz_f8yINNlqyrU48jCx-4ctPzihRKgde030w=s120-c-br100","Rating":0,"Description":"Hotel staff were friendly. They let me have guests which some of the hotels don't allow. Room was clean, and well organized. Price was on the reasonable side for what I got. It was on the first floor which made it very easy to access. Plus it was relatively near everything. There was a cute little restaurant right beside the place with a sweet family that I ate at a lot because it was so cheap and such great food for that price. I highly recommend this place.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"florence l","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/local-reviews/AJMZ0QcHwNVAhBufoo8LY9QJgA36LV2aF6lX0w2qy06Hm3sGcN-ZkjMp1R8g7n5EAkUzVe_g3g=s120-c-br100","Rating":0,"Description":"We stayed in the 2nd Okinawa (the one further from sule pagoda) thinking it was a good location : close from sule area and park but not too close from the pagoda 24h chanting mantras. |So it could have been a quiet place, if it was not fir the running teenage-team. No adults in here for the whole 2 days we have been in (so it is a very cool place for the young staff to work in!) But it then lacks of respect for the guests that wake up early and thus, go to bed early : singing loud, laughing louder, tv on...seemed to be in the staff house and not a guests house. The problem is the walls are very thin so you can't avoid the noise (We slept with ear plugs for 2 nights.)|Then dirty rooms (once more : teenage boys staff are often not the best to do this job!). Don't ever think to use the dusty mosquito nets if you tend to have allergy or are a minimum sensitive...|Good points though : breakfast, reception welcoming (also a teenage) and location.||To resume it is a good place for young people travelling on a budget (as Yangon is very expensive!!) but not much for thirties and/or older couples or single travellers that look for quiet places!!|","Images":null,"When":""}]

title: Shwe War Guest House
address: Street, Bogyoke Museum St, Yangon
descriptions: Down-to-earth rooms with flat-screens & minifridges in a relaxed guesthouse offering free breakfast.
user_reviews: [{"Name":"Jeremy B","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/local-reviews/AJMZ0Qdx0CtChWdL4amzhVtedU6JgNzs3A9KzPS8K998c7-u-mDeTb-7WQwuTD-PPX6BcVA5wg=s120-c-br100","Rating":0,"Description":"We booked the Shwe War Guest House for our Yangon leg of our honeymoon based on the TripAdvisor reviews, and unfortunately were very disappointed. We are used to living rough - we stayed at a couple local villages with no indoor plumbing, minimal electricity, and felt the accommodations were much nicer than at Shwe War.||We would give the staff a sold 4/5 stars, but the facilities and experience were a generous 2/5. ||The Good||We loved the staff! Everyone was lovely, attentive, flexible and kind. We were greeted warmly and with smiles every time we arrived or departed the hotel. They were quick to accommodate all of our needs and allowed a late check out at no extra cost. |||The Bad||Breakfast was pretty terrible. I guess we shouldn’t have ordered the more western breakfast and instead opted for local fare, which may have made a huge difference. White bread egg sandwich with velveta style American cheese that had cucumber and...ketchup?||The room was roomy and had most everything we needed, but the bed was rock hard and we found ants on our comforter after arriving. We were told that we had probably left something on the bed and that’s why ants had arrived. But whatever the case, this was a massive turn-off and left us feeling very uneasy about sleeping in the room. To their credit, they had a group of staff members to our room within minutes of making the phone call to complain and changed the linens and sprayed ant spray around the floor. We suggested a new room but they said ours was the best room.||The carpet also left a lot to be desired. It had lots of stains from glitter, glue(?), and dead bugs embedded into the fabric. The bathroom was awful as well. Shower hardware was broken so I had to squat to rinse my head and hold the shower for my wife who has an injured shoulder. There was also mold on the bathroom walls, sticky gunk on the mirror, and the sink drain barely worked. |||","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"OeivindSlaatto","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/local-reviews/AJMZ0QfCm-MBS7Itwd4h-55xcyygsVKq1IZbUTNyg17UKkQsT2C3oSXBlQ_-pGTl8imnrFVtVw=s120-c-br100","Rating":0,"Description":"I stayed here with my partner for 11 days while working in Yangon. The house has a warm, funny and friendly atmosphere and it seems that the always helpful, attentive and friendly staff enjoy their work, each other and their guests.|They made a good and beautiful breakfast and it was even possible to order fresh and tasty salad to the room which wasn't on their menu - or they provided esthetic arranged lunchboxes no matter how early in the morning we had to leave.|I often used the lobby to work where the fresh temperature and no disturbing traffic noise gave comfortable working conditions.||The place was clean and absolutely highly recommendable!","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"pauline ruby","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocJxcVoPLtwAla3JRstAcU_jp2HeuDVBXvGokSEaAbSKi0jdzQ=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"I really recommende this guest house. title: Cozy
address: No. 114, 13 Street Township, downtown, 11131, Yangon
user_reviews: [{"Name":"Charlie B","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/local-reviews/AJMZ0QeYuXGoFc9HnT35lAJ46cKDIsHY7nNIKUKz_f8yINNlqyrU48jCx-4ctPzihRKgde030w=s120-c-br100","Rating":0,"Description":"The rooms at Cozy Guest House are a bit small, and many possess no windows, but this is deep in Central Rangoon, and to be expected. They are spotless and cool, and very good at the price. This hotel comes into its own with the delightful, friendly staff and the wonderful, breakfast service: the best that we had in five weeks of travel. Consult with the front desk for your bus tickets and taxis for better rates than you will find at the agents. Very much recommended.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"chris s","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/local-reviews/AJMZ0QejddW0yoGeT8LnCjh-OGQgsf6YKqhof3HZA5-um4yCkQej85oCdMUmKPJmnowcu5Ag5w=s120-c-br100","Rating":0,"Description":"We spent 3 nights here. I was going to award 4* because the room smelt smoky at night: not their fault - it was the neighbours! But the service was so good and friendly - and they allowed us late check out 10pm for late flight (!!) at no charge, as the room wasn’t booked. So that has to be 5*. ||It’s good value, small basic room, clean, comfy bed, good aircon and hot water. For Yangon, in a good location, this is a great stay. Thank you.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"WATJEWE","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/local-reviews/AJMZ0QcKrc8e2JnTu8c7_hmoZKea10RMTDbKaR4QZbjFBwR43DXTBpqzkG_SGZrLD47rFdkvjQ=s120-c-br100","Rating":0,"Description":"Very nice guesthouse in the center of downtown city of Rangoon. Spacious and clean rooms (with or without window, you can ask what you want) with comfortable beds and hot shower. Breakfast on the rooftop is really top with fresh fruit and traditional - very good  food.||Staff - Kevin - is faboulous, he s very friendly and helpful, and takes care of everything. ||I absolutely recommend this guesthouse.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Martin O","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/local-reviews/AJMZ0Qf66pF81jsVXBxevYxxL5FsdlDsKAngAUpJVE-hAwai1rl8J0QnYqktKV3UGdpbmNlc_A=s120-c-br100","Rating":0,"Description":"Centrally located, just minutes away (on foot) from Chinatown 19th and 20th streets which had tasty street food and a great vibe. Rooms are clean and wifi worked fine. We loved the local breakfast on the 9th floor with a fantastic view of Shwedagon Pagoda. Staff is really nice and courteous although their English is rather limited.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Natalia P","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/local-reviews/AJMZ0QeNj0UTN0yIrCGyJ0JhWwDODOg5QjAH0gdfB9Ji-oFl0zWFI-YVmhNAr-FGLycdpIjFmw=s120-c-br100","Rating":0,"Description":"From the very first moment we were just in good hands! I never experienced such friendly, helpful and kind stuff like @ cozy guesthouse - Never! As my boyfriend got (really) sick, the staff looked so good after us - bringing us breakfast to the room, sandwiches, tea and water, even called a doctor who came to the hotel twice! We are speechless from the generosity! The rooms are clean, the bed comfortable, fair prices and the hotel is central! We highly recommend the cozy guesthouse! We're sure, you won't leave without a smile... Thanks very much for everything! Whenever we end up in yangon, we'll see you @ your guesthouse!","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Elaine J","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/local-reviews/AJMZ0QcHdm0oAuHtzPwzcwUtTqUfPbZXmYnyyN78cO7_Z2aHVLpBkIuu0olTbSpOuQZcPV9sYQ=s120-c-br100","Rating":0,"Description":"Our first ever visit to Yangon, we stayed at Cozy Guesthouse for its location in Chinatown and affordable price.  Little did we know what a warm treat it would be, hosted by generosity and kindness.  The beds were comfortable, the towels big and plush, the place tucked away from the street so that it was quiet.  Breakfast -- served on the 9th floor with a sweeping view of the city and Swedagon Pagoda! -- was a traditional breakfast of delicious home-cooked Burmese noodles, fresh sweet fruit and lots of delicious coffee and tea.  But the most wonderful treat was the staff -- always helpful and so accommodating, with a grace that made you feel part of the family (and this guesthouse is family-owned, with only 2 floors of guest rooms and the rest apartments occupied by families).||||On our last night at the hotel, we sat on the terrace outside the dining room to watch the sun set.  The host made a pot of tea to sip -- so thoughtful!  It was a beautiful evening.||||I'm missing Yangon, grateful for the hospitality of Cozy Guesthouse.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"ROZE J","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/local-reviews/AJMZ0QfnSFWXMd1oJu73a6IhdtgibYcjse2HKQTHeghNQd9Cyw8DYQQJZDCyh-TD68ehXuY-FA=s120-c-br100","Rating":0,"Description":"We stayed there 2 nights : clean room, hot shower that works well, no window but it’s common in Yangoon. The breakfast is burmese and in the rooftop with a nice view over the city. The staff is very helpful we change our plan and cancel our last night : they pay us back and arrange a night bus for us, they will do anything they can to help you !!","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Natasha D","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/local-reviews/AJMZ0QeNj0UTN0yIrCGyJ0JhWwDODOg5QjAH0gdfB9Ji-oFl0zWFI-YVmhNAr-FGLycdpIjFmw=s120-c-br100","Rating":0,"Description":"On arrival we had some discussions with the young boys on reception on the price which took a while to check us in. Then we had some problems with the aircon which took the boys a while to fix but eventually they managed. ||The following morning the owner greeted us and apologised for the misunderstanding and that he was going to upgrade us for the trouble. Amazing customer service which deserves 5 stars. ||The breakfast was Burmese style and you could have as much as you want. They also listen to requests. We had a very pleasant stay and would recommend it. Really good location in downtown Yangon.","Images":null,"When":""}]

title: Shwe Eain Si Guest House
address: No.34, Shwe Taung Tann, Street Lower Block, Yangon
user_reviews: [{"Name":"ThoChri","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/local-reviews/AJMZ0QeCck1CfANpZm9bBk3PHtP97Kh9k25HZfvq9yAWlN3BaIyjSHUPEfWkhAJmuYiJsH-_6g=s120-c-br100","Rating":0,"Description":"Accommodation in Myanmar is in general not especially good but quite pricey. |Same goes for this guesthouse. |We had a double room with shared bathroom and we have been lucky because, as I see it we got the biggest one. Still it is just a tiny bit bigger than the bed itself. At least it left some space to put our backpacks. The other rooms we've seen you had to climb onto the bed directly from the door. |There was no air circulation in our room, even though they had some kind of fan built into the wall, but there was no power plug on the other side, so it was completely useless. |As the doors were really thin and didn't close properly you could hear literally everything.  We don't mind much, but it gives you the feeling of sleeping in a dorm.||Apart from that the guesthouse was actually quite nice. The showers and toilets were okay and clean enough. |Breakfast was Myanmar but always different and good. |Staff was super friendly and would always help with calling a taxi or even booking an accommodation for us over the phone. ||This is probably not the best backpacker option in Yangon but it's not a bad one either. |The location directly in Chinatown is okay too. ||Enjoy your travels.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Arbox","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/local-reviews/AJMZ0QfjHmZg8gr7jpDgKhrh5KsR_Mq7L6pkVedvpKQz-f3LMiOd3OjI90CK4uLtF3wE59zZgA=s120-c-br100","Rating":0,"Description":"During the last couple of days in Myanmar, I stayed at 1415 guesthouse. In terms of how clean the place is, it is by far the best I have stayed in during my travels in Myanmar, given that I travel on a budget. Also, the place looked brand new and even smelled new. ||||On the downside, the rooms are more like cabins with a bed. Although I can perfectly live with this, the walls are quite thin. As you all know, fellow travellers are not always taking other guest into account, which might be a problem for you if you are a light sleeper.||||What definitively compensates, however, is the extremely friendly staff and breakfast. The staff was really kind, and the breakfast was different each day as well as served by staff with a smile!","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Lasse L","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/local-reviews/AJMZ0QdVsxDWqDDLG62Q3M3dmLlHORJs5jz0NWRJO3cP21KtRNPfosO7RpofjnbUgpyNjOTDew=s120-c-br100","Rating":0,"Description":"The Hotel is clean and friendly. The staffs are helpful. The Reception is open 24/7 and the hotel has CCTV for safety. The toilets and showers are clean and good. No looker available.||The cheap rooms are very small and the air conditioning is a fake. The AC is located outside from the room at the floor and a wall fan blows the cooled air into the rooms. The idea is to share the AC with other rooms. This didn't work in our room, so it was quite hot in the night.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Mary Jane P","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/local-reviews/AJMZ0Qf66pF81jsVXBxevYxxL5FsdlDsKAngAUpJVE-hAwai1rl8J0QnYqktKV3UGdpbmNlc_A=s120-c-br100","Rating":0,"Description":"rooms are clean but too small. Building was easy to find just look for the newest building in the area as all every other structures near the guesthouse were old and shabby.They have a very slow wifi connection and air-conditioning system are not good. They only have 1 big aircon upstairs and 2 aircon downstairs. Plus, they do not accept USD with folds and creases. even those with stamps from the banks. Just weird because we got our USD from banks and it is only here in Myanmar that they are so meticulous with their USD. breakfast served was very good. if you would be going out early in the morning you can ask them to prepare your breakfast early.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Angelina Y","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/local-reviews/AJMZ0QfjHmZg8gr7jpDgKhrh5KsR_Mq7L6pkVedvpKQz-f3LMiOd3OjI90CK4uLtF3wE59zZgA=s120-c-br100","Rating":0,"Description":"I had enjoyed the guest house in October 2015. The bathroom, lobby, dining room and the room itself were very clean and homy. It was very nice to stay for short term trip.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"DayTrader888","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/local-reviews/AJMZ0Qczn4VDfUM6-AtEt-6oaNazFa-i9Fy6kqPVfGIlPil6vJulEYyK8t930jZwOW4hD80mzw=s120-c-br100","Rating":0,"Description":"Stayed here 1 night. I liked to talk to Maria, she and her husband were sooo nice! Maria Helped me as well with my Train Ride to Mumbai after- thank you so much again!||The rooms were clean and functional, i Can recommand||........................................................","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Sanjeewa Herath","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVXQGON59ovCUsF9CYHTzRgB-JRAr9UQ6oNZylUGzmiJXneUFLB=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"Good for budget travelers. Clean rooms, have hot /cold shower. No insects, no mosquitoes. Have small dining place too. Serve beakfast included in room rate. But its not that what usual western breakfast. They serve fried rice and noodles( in Myanmar they eat rice/ noodles all the three meals ) you can get toast butter and jam on request. ( two slice) There are no good places around here to eat. But you can have good fresh fruits from street vendor very cheap. rooms rate abot $20. In june 2017.  Staff is very helpful , find english speaking in bit challenging. But they undestand. I used google translate app. It worked. They do laundry too. Reasonable price.  also they have generator  too so power cut wont be a problem. Close to the air port. You can get taxi from here to downtown about 5000 to 8000 kyt. Depending on time. Morning is cheap. There is kareoki bar near by. title: Three Seasons Guesthouse
address: No. 88,first floor, 52nd St, Pazuntaung Township
user_reviews: [{"Name":"Elizabeth L","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/local-reviews/AJMZ0QcHdm0oAuHtzPwzcwUtTqUfPbZXmYnyyN78cO7_Z2aHVLpBkIuu0olTbSpOuQZcPV9sYQ=s120-c-br100","Rating":0,"Description":"This is a solid budget family-run small hotel in a good location.  The family is incredibly warm and helpful and it's on a small street so the noise is not bad at all.  The rooms are large but a bit run down and dark, although clean and functional.  The air condioning and wifi were reliably good.  This is a fine hotel if you're not planning to spend a lot of time in the room.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Mart S","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/local-reviews/AJMZ0Qf66pF81jsVXBxevYxxL5FsdlDsKAngAUpJVE-hAwai1rl8J0QnYqktKV3UGdpbmNlc_A=s120-c-br100","Rating":0,"Description":"We stayed in the upper rooms private baths some with a sort of window. The bathrooms are older and have a few leaks. It's an older house with lots of wood and high ceilings and has only about 8 or 9 rental rooms.  Ms Hla Hla was very helpful as was the staff. A good breakfast was served in the dinning / breakfast room. I understand Yagon hotels are priced on the high side and this falls into that category.  I would recommend this hotel but it is priced about $10 too high.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"AmbreBernard","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/local-reviews/AJMZ0QfjHmZg8gr7jpDgKhrh5KsR_Mq7L6pkVedvpKQz-f3LMiOd3OjI90CK4uLtF3wE59zZgA=s120-c-br100","Rating":0,"Description":"We were really happy to have stayed in this charming house. The reception is made of wood and has a really homely feel to it. The location in first glance doesn't seem great, but it's acrually fantastic! You are located in a nice area of Yangoon populated by clean street food vendors. The hotel staff are extremely helpful and kind. Would recommend.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Sandrine J","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/local-reviews/AJMZ0QeFH6dzZjd_ZFLhXHZKibEzXEy8hWzFB4Qa7PutLe3CnO2G7yVfjd4VSabiCQwQYo5W-g=s120-c-br100","Rating":0,"Description":"You get into Yangon mode as soon as you arrive at Three Seasons Hotel. The laid-back atmosphere in a quiet yet central part of the city, the simple rooms with fans on the ceilings, the eggs and papaya for breakfast ( room and breakfast ready even if you arrive at 5 am ;)). In the evening just sit on the bench near the front door, listen to the sounds of the city, smell the flowers  and play with the kittens while chatting to the owner or the friendly guy who works there. We took a night bus and got a nice pic nic to take away.  I will go back for sure :)","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Michelle M","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/local-reviews/AJMZ0Qf66pF81jsVXBxevYxxL5FsdlDsKAngAUpJVE-hAwai1rl8J0QnYqktKV3UGdpbmNlc_A=s120-c-br100","Rating":0,"Description":"Recently, I visited Three Seasons Hotel after many years: 13 to be exact, my first time to travel to Myanmar.  Everything is the same as in January 2006 at Three Seasons Hotel.  The warmth and friendliness are still the same. It is also atmospheric with its dark teak interior which is cool and inviting after being in the summer heat.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Ken C","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/local-reviews/AJMZ0QdCjMUwIiBikRhCLHgN_0vyGAo1GvT8DEukiKQb1ujC_eFsFjYrQ0OvLoSxPtqmCdgvFA=s120-c-br100","Rating":0,"Description":"We flew into Yangon and were met at the airport by the hotel driver, given the warmest of welcomes at the hotel, had a lovely big room with air con and fridge, and ate delicious breakfasts in the morning. A month later, having toured Myanmar, we were taken back to the airport - amazing service, one of the best.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Itamar T","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/local-reviews/AJMZ0QfsnvlNO8mgROWsxiGYBmc-FMApm47le01WrNgEyYNYqUPw1j7nx-COV-HLlhXF8VUXQQ=s120-c-br100","Rating":0,"Description":"Really good hotel. Pretty new furniture and good room! The hotel has a good breakfast and tha costumers are kindly. During your stay at the hotel rent a bicycle  and go to explore the town. It cost 50 bath the day use.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"John S","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/local-reviews/AJMZ0Qdx0CtChWdL4amzhVtedU6JgNzs3A9KzPS8K998c7-u-mDeTb-7WQwuTD-PPX6BcVA5wg=s120-c-br100","Rating":0,"Description":"Overall a good experience. The breakfasts were amazing and the people who ran the guesthouse were extremely nice and helpful. The boss always dodge from us and send just his employees that didn’t know English at all.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Brice L","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/local-reviews/AJMZ0QfHhPp0vyvo1Wo3WY4NH1G5QOPAHGBMv_XiebXLZtHzVwVa3wkRhb3dykyKrUCZPlawDA=s120-c-br100","Rating":0,"Description":"Horrible place. Dirty and no windows. You can easily start a conversation with your neighbors. The worst thing about this accommodation is the unfriendly manager who prefers counting and recounting his money instead of doing anything else. |He prefers delegating (not to say anything else) his duties to a 10 years old boy who sleeps at night directly on the lobby's floor. |I have been traveling across South East Asia and never experienced that.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Anthonybht","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/local-reviews/AJMZ0QfjHmZg8gr7jpDgKhrh5KsR_Mq7L6pkVedvpKQz-f3LMiOd3OjI90CK4uLtF3wE59zZgA=s120-c-br100","Rating":0,"Description":"This place is a nightmare! ||This place is running down, not comfortable, dirty, no able to have a shower or flush the toilet cause no water in tank. ||Room is creepy and they have bed bugs all over! ||We had to spend 50$ to clean all our stuff and bags cause in the morning we noticed that we had bite all over our body and bugs in our bags after two nights here and they clearly now about it... ||we ask for. Refund for the night we run away this place and suddenly the reception guys didn’t talk English anymore... ||if you want an advice do not stay here even if the price is cheap to avoid a lot of trouble!","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Lucas N","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/local-reviews/AJMZ0QdVsxDWqDDLG62Q3M3dmLlHORJs5jz0NWRJO3cP21KtRNPfosO7RpofjnbUgpyNjOTDew=s120-c-br100","Rating":0,"Description":"I stayed at the guest house early July 2017. I had just flown in to yangon from paris and the idea was to have a place to rest our heads while we waited to take the night bus to kalaw. ||To be honest I wasn't expecting much, we chose this place that appeared the the cheap section of our guide book. ||Regardless of what the purpose of the visit, there are standards and limits. Paying $23 i was really surprised by the room ... The room was like a jail cell, barely any room to move. The bed sheets where not clean (dead ants in the sheets), the bathroom was also an experience ...||When you book they don't tell you that there are two types of double rooms, double with bathroom and double with shared bathroom. If you have to stay here take the private bathroom, the share bathroom is really really not nice. The only issue is that by the time you have payed the price for the double with bathroom you might as well pay an extra $4-$5 to stay in a much much nicer place (the vibe inn)||||The only saving grace for this place is that the staff is very friendly, but they are not $27 dollars friendly.||||Small side note, if you arrive early ..... you pay $3 to check in early ..... even if the hotel is 100% empty ....||All in all not worth even a stop over unless you have no other choice","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Clara V","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/local-reviews/AJMZ0QeYuXGoFc9HnT35lAJ46cKDIsHY7nNIKUKz_f8yINNlqyrU48jCx-4ctPzihRKgde030w=s120-c-br100","Rating":0,"Description":"I must first point out that the staff are lovely and really try their best to make your stay pleasant. However, it does not justify the fact that you pay over 15$ (if not more) to stay in a coffin room (our room was 4sqm - could barely fit our backpacks and ourselves at the same time!) with no windows. The whole place stinks and there is no air at all (since there are no windows anywhere!). There is one shared bathroom for the 8 rooms of the hotel, and it is truly disagreeable to take a shower there. There is a huge rusty tank of murky water, supposedly where the shower water comes from, and there are no windows to air the place so it smells old and moldy. The breakfast is not bad, if you like eating local (we had fish noodle soup) but not great coffee (as everywhere in Myanmar). ||Overall, I would warn travellers not to stay at this guesthouse.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Kyla K","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/local-reviews/AJMZ0QdCjMUwIiBikRhCLHgN_0vyGAo1GvT8DEukiKQb1ujC_eFsFjYrQ0OvLoSxPtqmCdgvFA=s120-c-br100","Rating":0,"Description":"The staff were friendly and nice enough. Very small rooms, and only one bathroom to share between about 6 rooms.  Maybe to be expected for the price though?  At about 4:45am the staff were getting up and ready for the day I assume, and were ridiculously loud.  To the point of almost yelling and coughing and up and down the halls.  I couldn't get back to sleep and ended up giving up my second night I had already paid for to find a new room.  Not a usual move of mine but it was worth it as I found a much better spot in the same price point.  An ok location and the air conditioning is new and works well (also towels provided) but would not stay again due to how loud it was and the poor bathroom facilities.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"sebastian osval... S","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/local-reviews/AJMZ0QeSe9ibNVY65MpgeQh70I370foM0-7tEPyVc9CIfSq5Ekli093sZJVPBoLD5d5qPK_2rw=s120-c-br100","Rating":0,"Description":"We reserve the hotel and because it has an  almost identical name than other hotel two Blocks away with good reputation. It is clearly a scam since some comments say the same thing. Our  “special room” as it was called seemed like a jail. You would lock the door with a huge padlock they provided you. The room was a nightmare: very dirty and disgusting looking, like it was never ever cleaned. It smelled like mold and dirt very strongly. There was garbage under the tv shelve and behind the toilet as you can see in pictures. The windows were broken and there were rat poop in them.We just look for another hotel and escape of this prison as soon as possible, loosing all our money (we paid 3 nights).The worst hotel that I was in my life","Images":null,"When":""}]

title: The Sat
address: Q4FW+XXP The Sat, Lanmadaw St, Yangon
user_reviews:
[{"Name":"Jack R","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/local-reviews/AJMZ0Qdx0CtChWdL4amzhVtedU6JgNzs3A9KzPS8K998c7-u-mDeTb-7WQwuTD-PPX6BcVA5wg=s120-c-br100","Rating":0,"Description":"The location is good although on a very busy corner. Travel time to/from airport around 40 - 70 minutes depending on the traffic. Staff is very friendly and helpful. Rooms on the reception floor were small but wifi was strong. Rooms on the top floor were larger but wifi was weaker. Breakfast was typical budget hotel breakfast. Shared bathrooms were not a problem at all. If you travel on a budget and are ok with budget accomodations, then you will like it here. Reception is up a flight of stairs so if you travel heavy or have mobility issues, this place may not be for you. I stayed here twice on my trip and would stay again.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Patrick S","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/local-reviews/AJMZ0Qd0Gzx7-o-W0qn7F-oHhorx-ann6UFYRniBmE7Ar1MhRFtO-x6vY7U2LNCPC1lcQidkpw=s120-c-br100","Rating":0,"Description":"If you are traveling on a budget, then the SAT Yangon is definitely the place to go to!||||Ideally located in the heart of downtown, you are close to lots of shops, banks, pharmacies, restaurants, and the 19th street BBQ scene.||||The friendly and helpful staff is what makes the difference at this guest house. They are so nice and will do everything in their power to make sure you have a pleasant stay. My plane was landing at 5:45am and of course my room wasn't ready this early in the morning. Well, they provided another room so I could rest and I was able to move in my room later that afternoon.||||Breakfast was different every morning and it was delicious. And the wifi worked well.||||The guest house is on a very busy street corner, so it can be quite noisy at times. Try to book room 204, which has no window. Spent two nights in that room and I slept very well. Also, the A/C in room 204 is nice and doesn't make much noise.||||The staff was there to help me out with everything, from booking a driver to pick me up from the airport or take me to the bus station, to booking bus tickets, to offering suggestions for places to eat. They were awesome throughout my stay.||||The SAT Yangon is clean guest house. The only problem is with the Italian bathroom, with the showers so close to the toilets. As soon as someone showers, then everything gets wet and it's hard to keep that looking good. But other than that, the rest of the property was always super clean.||||I would go back in a heartbeat if I ever return to Yangon!","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Signe C","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/local-reviews/AJMZ0QeFH6dzZjd_ZFLhXHZKibEzXEy8hWzFB4Qa7PutLe3CnO2G7yVfjd4VSabiCQwQYo5W-g=s120-c-br100","Rating":0,"Description":"This place is an amazing option, if you want to stay close to it all. |The ting we liked most was the staff and the cleanliness. |There are so many toilets with showers, that you will never have to wait.|Breakfast is good and simple, we never left the hostel hungry.|But the best thing was the staff. I have never meet so smiling and helpful staff. |They belong at a 5 star hotel. Wow, just wow !!!|Only small thing, if you are bad with stairs and don’t like noise. Don’t go here. |You will hear the traffic. But we felt it as part of the charm. |A mix between roosters and horns is what you will hear. |I guess they sell them ;) |I would go back.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Tom Skelton","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWY-qWNm23XgfXpwgH6EZU4S6LVXMGrN8qoh0qsVY2lNPeKpzzV5w=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"A really friendly and convenient place to stay in the heart of downtown Yangon. The staff were simply brilliant. Rooms were light and airy and we had both a/c and fan. The shared bathrooms were totally fine. Breakfast was good and they met my vegan needs. Would happily return here again.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"April S","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/local-reviews/AJMZ0QfjHmZg8gr7jpDgKhrh5KsR_Mq7L6pkVedvpKQz-f3LMiOd3OjI90CK4uLtF3wE59zZgA=s120-c-br100","Rating":0,"Description":"Arriving on the overnight train from Bagan, we got to our hostel at around 6 am and were given an early check in and breakfast. We stayed in a superior twin room, with two beds, minibar access, and towels. The location of the toilets and showers were a bit weird as you have to trek past the lobby area to get to it. ||The receptionists at the desks were extremely helpful: they gave us suggestions for places to go, helped us arrange transport to the airport, and printed a few documents for my friend for free. ||Keep in mind this is not a place I would recommend if you are used to staying at  higher end hostels or hotels. The beds can be a bit rigid (though I slept fine) and the streets can get busy at night. ||The breakfast was great and we sampled different burmese dishes during our stay. The amazing service alone made up for the minor inconveniences of the noisy bustle of a busy street and having to walk past the lobby  (only a few steps) in a towel after your shower.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Kira C","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/local-reviews/AJMZ0QdCjMUwIiBikRhCLHgN_0vyGAo1GvT8DEukiKQb1ujC_eFsFjYrQ0OvLoSxPtqmCdgvFA=s120-c-br100","Rating":0,"Description":"I stayed for a weekend in Yangon while my boyfriend was visiting from Hong Kong. The location, right on a street corner, within very reasonable walking distance of 19th street, Bogyoke market and even the train station - is ideal. Some of the staircases are challenging and feel a little rickety coming down to the bathrooms, and the initial stair up to the hostel is steep and long, but the rooms are efficient, some have great windows looking onto the bustle of the street outside, and the breakfast is good. Great if you're on a budget and want a wonderful staff and strong wifi (a rarity, it seems, throughout Yangon).","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Subramanyam V","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/local-reviews/AJMZ0QeFH6dzZjd_ZFLhXHZKibEzXEy8hWzFB4Qa7PutLe3CnO2G7yVfjd4VSabiCQwQYo5W-g=s120-c-br100","Rating":0,"Description":"Located in a busy Chinatown area, this isn't too far from all attractions in downtown Yangon.  The host will share a tourist map and point out major ones, nearby.  The place is neat and clean. The bathrooms are shared and cleaned regularly. Breakfast was simple. No eggs though. Wi-Fi was excellent. All in all, a decent place with great service.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Paulo AO","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocJwjL7wGH3-qEUyA1MJxroXBbsuXT44Cw2JDa4Bo0mR467H-A=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":1,"Description":"Not that clean, not that silent and not that cheap.

The location is a must but because the building is not isolated you have to deal with the noise from the street.

The room has AC but if you turn it on it seems that you have a 1976 Chevrolet in your room. Because of the noise we had to turn it off. We used the fan, it was noisy too but we were already in a survival mode.

At the breakfast room there were a lady smoking. The staff that was there didn't say anything so we had to "enjoy" the toasts and pineapple with tobacco. By the way the breakfast is OK. Tea, toasts with butter and/or jam and pineapple.

Regarding cleaning. It's OK but don't expect a super clean place with staff dedicated all day.

We paid 17$ for a night. Compared to other hostels in the same location this hostel is doesn't worth more than 12$.

Overrated, overpriced, overnoisy, oversmoky.","Images":null,"When":""}]

title: Golden Guest Inn
address: near Than Lann Bus Stop, 182 Insein Rd, Yangon
descriptions: Plain rooms in an unassuming guesthouse with complimentary Wi-Fi & breakfast, plus a garden.
user_reviews: [{"Name":"Arnel Castillo","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocIN9Nl_yx099Eg1gO_f_KLgwREr4ttqA1HS93faPgcsHom8Ug=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"I would want to share our wonderful experience in Yangon, Myanmar. We went there last March 14 to March 17, 2019 to do Leaders Training Weekend. Since it is our first time in Myanmar we don't know the place but our friend Teacher Mang recommended us to stay in Golden Guest Inn and it was a great experience for me and my wife. First, let us start with the price, for less than US$150 for 4 days and 3 nights it is definitely a winner. Plus lots of freebies in the room like water, coffee, tea etc. The reception is very accommodating and Ted was very helpful in booking our Grab wherever we go. He always makes it a point that the driver knows where to take us and even talks to the driver just to be sure. Our room is always kept clean, tidy with clean sheets. Our friends who visited us were surprised with how affordable and yet our room is big enough, comfortable and safe.  We definitely recommended Golden Guest Inn to our friends who are visiting Yangon and will continue to recommend them because its like our second home away from the Philippines. You will definitely prove me right once you visited and stayed in Golden Guest Inn.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Raymond L","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/local-reviews/AJMZ0QfnSFWXMd1oJu73a6IhdtgibYcjse2HKQTHeghNQd9Cyw8DYQQJZDCyh-TD68ehXuY-FA=s120-c-br100","Rating":0,"Description":"Pleasant and clean hotel. though amidst a busy street, the rooms are actually well enclosed behind the building, totally sound proof from the cars and honks outside.||||Rooms are clean with bunch of freebies (drinks, coffee) included. Nothing to complain about. ||||The family that owns the hotel are extremely friendly and approachable. They were willing to cater to my last minute request and prepared a room for my family in a short time when I needed one impromptu. ||||The staffs are very helpful with luggage and what nots. ||||I would highly recommend staying here!||||ps. I stayed here on the 1st day and 4th day of my Myanmar trip. enjoyed it!  thank you!||||the rooms are much better than my photo. the photo don't do justice. ||||👍👍👍💯","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Mark S","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/local-reviews/AJMZ0Qf66pF81jsVXBxevYxxL5FsdlDsKAngAUpJVE-hAwai1rl8J0QnYqktKV3UGdpbmNlc_A=s120-c-br100","Rating":0,"Description":"This hotel is not flashy or glamorous. Instead it’s a very comfortable and convenient home away from home. ||The reason for my enthusiasm is the impeccable care and attention given by two generations of owners who really go out of their way to make guests’ lives as easy as possible. An extension of that care are the features of the super clean rooms - very comfortable beds with fresh crisp linens every day. Excellent WiFi throughout, an unusual range of complimentary beverages, restocked daily, and appliances that always work.  ||Beside the friendly and helpful staff, there has never been a time when at least one of the owners was not on site and ready to help with any additional needs or questions. ||Even though I’m not a breakfast person, the excellent breakfast, freshly made to order also deserves special mention.||I highly recommend Golden Guest Inn and will definitely book it for our next stay in Yangon.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"jadragard","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/local-reviews/AJMZ0Qc_m0BOt0e288CC5xVhlFJeGbeLoq1HoB7h5IAKHAwOrWyFaFWxIwsJ8EDSK3zkB1-qng=s120-c-br100","Rating":0,"Description":"The best with this hotel is the family that owns it, they are so helpful with everything. The room is large and completely quiet (which you would not expect on a busy street). Amidst all more city like buildings this is an oasis. The breakfast is fantastic. It is like a very good traveller kind of place, I travelled for work and it was equally good. Wifi is good, power cuts covered rapidly by the generator, shower and bathroom clean and everything works. I would surely stay here next time as well.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Mark Robinette","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjW_TjqTCCo6Swqfwp0Xhq7hqC_d8aZz4ZMWeE7OkJ70BjWeNxrHqw=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"What a wonderful discovery in Yangon. The owner and manager Tet made us feel so very welcome and took care of all our needs. We quickly discovered this was the chosen destination of many travelers who make regular trips to Yangon. The food is wonderful, the rooms are clean and cool and the staff is a family you will enjoy. Tired of staying at places where you cannot understand the staff, the Golden Guest Inn management speaks fluent English and is very helpful in understanding local customs and even conducting business.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Michael Chan","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVsuugxulTL_utZjCyX4nZreWj0aKe6tdonWvLviBCkCSaN8sX7jA=s120-c-rp-mo-ba6-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"This is a hotel that I've been recently introduced to, and it has not disappointed at all. It's a converted colonial house, with rooms in both the front and back wings. Rooms are generous, and though the furniture may be classic teak wood, the amenities are not lacking at all: coffee and tea sachets, coffee maker + coffee powder + filter paper without extra charge! The power strips are universal so you don't have to worry about the type of plugs you have. Breakfast is ordered thru a menu, where both western and local breakfast is available. The only reason that I did not give it a full 5 stars was that it's a little out of the way for me. I'm a business traveller who had most meetings around town and surrounding. Still, this is a place no traveller should miss!","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Teej Jae","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVDL4Cmqg9Qzh5ZCLMvo2NG5aRICHQn7dP4XrTdeasT-x2wExs=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Golden Guest Inn is a safe and secure environment. I never once had to worry about my luggage getting stolen, because the owner's wife personally keeps an eye on the housekeepers. The manager, Ted, is a sweetheart, and takes care of any need or want you may have. There is an ATM located conveniently inside the inn. Hot showers are available! The air conditioning is amazing especially during Myanmar's notorious hot season. During Water Festival (Myanmar's New Year), there is an amazing restaurant next door that is one of the only restaurants open in the entire city! The bus stop is literally outside the property which makes getting downtown a breeze. There is a small convenient store a few hundred feet away, and an amazing grocery store within walking distance of .8 miles (1.28 km) away. The rooms are quiet which ensures a full rest. I highly reccomend  Golden Guest Inn be your next stay!","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Tomas Ruhland","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUI4Ov-01lFMC16XKOCyg8l3GzShiRT_hI6hfXpZJCUMmpn8FLhWA=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"LOVE this place! Every room has a fridge, a/c unit and nice sized tv.\nThe wifi quality is the best I have ever experienced anywhere in Yangon. There is much more space here compared to downtown hostels. The staff were so flexible in meeting our needs!","Images":null,"When":""}]

There are plenty of food shops around as well. U can go by walk to nearby places.
The hostel staff are responsive,  check in was easy and quick. They have a food court, a good breakfast in the morning.
The room was decent, with warm water and ac up to the mark.
They also arranged for the drop off at the airport with 30k kyat.
There are no elevators in the hostel, and climbing up to the 4th floor with luggage is not easy, especially for the old ones.
I would totally recommend this place for a short stay.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPxBK4Ig8gFH80zb9j4ZA5Vh-ZY4XOLRc0CLVw&fid=0x0:0x590c99c6288c1026"],"When":"2024-12-22"},{"Name":"jaime bol (jaime bol)","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWyMq8eV9HYwHc7Uy_-o95DVDLSl2xio8mQrDyHae8-GFIVNk5w=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":1,"Description":"I don't recommend it

title: White House Hotel
address: No. 69/71 Konzaydan Street
descriptions: Low-key rooms, some with sitting areas, in a down-to-earth hotel featuring a halal restaurant.
user_reviews:
[{"Name":"Sackhy L","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/local-reviews/AJMZ0QeFH6dzZjd_ZFLhXHZKibEzXEy8hWzFB4Qa7PutLe3CnO2G7yVfjd4VSabiCQwQYo5W-g=s120-c-br100","Rating":0,"Description":"I booked two nights, then ended up staying four more nights. title: Hotel Accord
address: No. 69 Damar Yone Street, Myay Ni Gone, Yangon 11111
descriptions: Simple rooms & suites in a casual hotel offering an airy restaurant & free breakfast.
user_reviews:
[{"Name":"Myo Thet Kyu","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVqTMMPEWmJ_ABi8T-HDgXv57cXEFzvKmnHX-TvAVRICPeniuc=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":2,"Description":"just checked-in. although location is good, the room is dirty. Dusts on the desks and the tables. And bedsheets got some stains. Try to call the reception but the in-room phone line is not working. The housekeeper came and changed the bedsheets. But the bedsheets he brought still gots some stains on it. After  he saw the stains on the new bedsheet he brought, he asked me if I still want the new sheet. he continued saying that all the bedsheets will be like this although they got it from the new laundry bag. I friendly asked if they used the outsourced service for laundry, he answered yes. I friendly told him may be the laundry service place is not working properly.. still the housekeeper resists that the laundry service they used is used by most of the famous hotels in town. I am not expecting the best top notch services but after tiring long trip, I want the place I paid for still offer the bare minimum services like clean bed sheets, a working phone line, and the clean tables and desks.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Anthony Policano","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWpjNo3VkwJLEQ-xqjh9_tk0PdvBE7vL9LDPnr7RNtrXramme0O=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"Great hotel, great staff, great breakfast buffet (nice fruit plate for vegans), great central location next to a bustling local market, and always-on power with backup generator.

I stayed there twice, and my only complaint is that the first time my room was very small: for two people, we felt really cramped and couldn’t even walk past each other without someone jumping onto the bed to move out of the way (room 505), and one side of the bed didn’t have a table, and plugs behind the bed were difficult to access. The second time, the room (206) was at least a meter wider, had two bedside tables, and easy to reach plugs, which made all the difference! Another tiny complaint is that they offer water bottles but no easy-access to a more eco-friendly water refill station, but I asked the staff at the kitchen to help me and that always obliged (albeit with discomfort on their faces). Let’s do our part to use less single-use plastics!!

Other than that, I loved it.

TIP: there are a number of money changers nearby, but I only found one to sell my leftover MMK to for USD on departure, called WK at the bigger junction SW of the hotel.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Jordi Clement","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjV1SqkxobNOsWyLwPMFxQ_2731hIMK-DSX3qSmusyJBx1Xj1peTUQ=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":3,"Description":"So far so good. From my opinion too much money for the value but it was acceptable for Myanmar standards.
The breakfast was very nice and the staff kind and helpful. The room could be in better conditions and maintenance but as well, ok.. The location is nice.
The annoying thing was the elevator/ascensor: there's only one for the whole hotel so get ready to wait long periods of time to use it, all the staff is using it continuously through all day, up and down and down to up.. It's always busy with workers. The costumers will need to wait.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Trip.com Member","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/local-reviews/AJMZ0QeCck1CfANpZm9bBk3PHtP97Kh9k25HZfvq9yAWlN3BaIyjSHUPEfWkhAJmuYiJsH-_6g=s120-c-br100","Rating":0,"Description":"Location in the city center Near hotel has local market Nice and good staff Hotel convince","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Exploration773782","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/local-reviews/AJMZ0QcHdm0oAuHtzPwzcwUtTqUfPbZXmYnyyN78cO7_Z2aHVLpBkIuu0olTbSpOuQZcPV9sYQ=s120-c-br100","Rating":0,"Description":"I stayed there 19 nighs. There are some good points (mostly) and a few bad ones. Fistly the staff is very friendly and supportive. There can be no complaints about them. Secondly the management acted very responsible, when I was in a health danger situation. I am very thankful to them for that. The bad points: One Aircon was not working and I was told beyond repair. I waited for a word of excuse (or even compensation) by the General Manger Mr. Smith Tin Win Aye, but that never happened. Finally i asked 2 time for an appointment, only to hear that "he is not free" "he is busy". Is that a proper way to behave by a GM ? I dont thinks so. Finally it must be mentioned that I could hear every word from the guests below my room. But total lack of sound isolation is common in Yangon.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Donna Fleur Raw","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWG_oDPIUYbMJOXtLU3sC9asIF8KV1bfiXDBSAgItIwke1D1LSh=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"I had originally planned to stay at the Hotel Accord for a only few days until I found more permanent accommodation since moving to Yangon. Unfortunately my search for an apartment took longer than expected, but the hotel’s wonderful staff and management have gone the extra mile to accommodate me for my unexpected longer stay. The hotel is run excellently with the utmost professionalism, while at the same time being so friendly and caring to its guests. The rooms are well furnished, clean, and modern. The hotels restaurant provides delicious meals too! Overall this place has been my home away from home- I highly recommend it!","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Jim L","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/local-reviews/AJMZ0Qdx0CtChWdL4amzhVtedU6JgNzs3A9KzPS8K998c7-u-mDeTb-7WQwuTD-PPX6BcVA5wg=s120-c-br100","Rating":0,"Description":"I stayed at this hotel for two weeks. I paid for the two room suite but it still only cost me $70 US per night. Excellent value. It is located in a market area which might be a bit off putting for some but I loved the local interaction. Everything in the room worked and the beds are comfortable. Breakfast was included but fairly poor. Chose to eat a local stalls outside the hotel. Hotel is about 20 minutes walk from Shwedagon and you can easily get taxis. One tip use the grab app to book taxis. Works so well and you know the price when you book. Taxis are safe and very cheap. Reception was good and they do speak some English.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Mallika R","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/local-reviews/AJMZ0Qf66pF81jsVXBxevYxxL5FsdlDsKAngAUpJVE-hAwai1rl8J0QnYqktKV3UGdpbmNlc_A=s120-c-br100","Rating":0,"Description":"We stayed at the start and end of our trip and had contrasting experiences. The 5th floor room was very spacious, clean with good view while the 6th floor room was too small, smelling of cigarette (unless AC was on), facing back street of an apartment filled with garbage and lots of crows. Hotel was booked through package so cant comment on price. ||The staff was very helpful and even let us use the microwave for outside food we had got. Location is good and close to the Shwedagon pagoda and reasonable distance to Scott market.  Reception even helped us to book a taxi and lent umbrellas whenever we went out. They also allowed us to check out 2 hours later as we had an evening plane out of Yangoon.||Restaurant has minimal options, unfortunately not much local Burmese flavors and only 1 option for vegetarians. Breakfast was the usual spread. The place is very centrally located and has lots of eating options around from eateries to road side food.","Images":null,"When":""}]

title: Esperado Lake View Hotel
address: Q5VC+885 Esperado Lake View Hotel, No.23 Kan Yeik Tha Rd, Yangon 11221
descriptions: Relaxed hotel with free breakfast, plus a spa & a rooftop bar with live music on the weekends.
user_reviews:
[{"Name":"Naw Seng Awng (Naw Naw)","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjV4Leoj14WqpS408sR_UqqY3wR0bqziO_oFRVuajzmNS3yS4rLdGA=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"Had a really good stay at Esperado Lake View Hotel! The location is a big plus too. It’s right near Kandawgyi Lake, so if you like jogging in the morning, it’s perfect. Oh, and there’s a teahouse inside the hotel that’s honestly so good! The tea and snacks are delicious and super affordable.

Definitely a solid choice if you’re looking for a nice place to stay in Yangon!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipO9sW4JcbxLwwOh1ONcxAxWOWdsnidmwbuoodxW&fid=0x0:0xb807c82813413de5"],"When":"2025-2-14"},{"Name":"Thu Prit","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWRhc-ifqrhbB4KCBPZTs6f2FkvLpbB_ETVtztP1lmXaDi8_P8=s120-c-rp-mo-ba2-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"The rooftop has a great view, but lack in decoration, in order to attract more visitors and tourists, there should be more lounge space, light decoration and bar decoration. Downstairs restaurant is so loud, well most of the time I don’t understand so I don’t really care. Some of the reception desk staff are so lovely and nice with great smile. Front door assistances are so helpful.. even helping me in across the busy street.

The staff services are worth staying there. Thank you all the staff for helping us in every need. Good location near Myanmar Plaza.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Dave P","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/local-reviews/AJMZ0Qczn4VDfUM6-AtEt-6oaNazFa-i9Fy6kqPVfGIlPil6vJulEYyK8t930jZwOW4hD80mzw=s120-c-br100","Rating":0,"Description":"We stayed at Yankin on our first night in Myanmar - after a long travel (2 days from UK via HK) we were late getting in. Reception was dealt with quickly, and although the restaurant was closed, they found some beers for us, and allowed us to use the facilities to eat food which we obtained from nearby. Rooms were good, clean and well equipped. Breakfast was great, with omelettes cooked to order as well as the usual buffet fare. We travelled rounf Myanmar and returned to this hotel 2 weeks later to the same standard of service. Can't comment on the nearby ameneties, or the area in general as we were merely 'passing through' and needed a bed for the night. Overall, a good hotel with everything you need for a short stay. Probably not best location if you want a week here, but for us it was ideal. (We stayed in March, but Trip Advisor is playing up and keeps defaulting to todays date!)","Images":null,"When":""}]

Room/ 3 Stars - made a reservation with a confirmation of Premier room with king bed size in advance but they gave me twin joint bed, normally I won’t have any problem either King or twins Zipped bed however under the twin zipped bed, they placed normal sponge sheets which very hot and uncomfortable to sleep on. title: Hotel Bond
address: 49 Hledan Street, Yangon
descriptions: Unfussy quarters, some with balconies, in an unassuming hotel offering a cafe & free Wi-Fi.
user_reviews:
[{"Name":"Trip.com Member","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/local-reviews/AJMZ0QeCck1CfANpZm9bBk3PHtP97Kh9k25HZfvq9yAWlN3BaIyjSHUPEfWkhAJmuYiJsH-_6g=s120-c-br100","Rating":0,"Description":"A budget hotel with very friendly and helpful staff, offering a good breakfast with a buffet. Note that the rooms have a shared bathroom, which should be taken into account. The internet connection can occasionally be interrupted, so it’s better to have your own SIM card for work","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Matthew Ortiz","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXRWq-BNP10zsikF7cEz4hQxZ-OBwASD31FTupiRHyjoAXQoc0=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":2,"Description":"At first it looks like a very good deal, a whole apartment with 2 bedrooms and 2 bathrooms for a low price.  When you see how dirty it is then the price makes sense.

But, you are given 2 doorlocks for the two bedroons, there is no doorlock to the main living room.  At firsr it seemed like just a strange inconvenience because they are "changing locks" but in hindsight I think this is just a socially acceptable excuse but in hindsight I believe it to be deception (based on their behavior of just entering the room when they feel like it.

The first time my wife was surprised and they were blessed by getting to see to much of her.  After that they kept coming back again and again under the guise of being extra helpful.

Their behavior was polite but I found it completely unacceptable.  At night I  dragged the couch in front of the door and put another chair on top of it and leaned against the door so that if someone tried to push the door opened then the chair should fall off and make a loud noise and alert me that someone was trying to enter the room at night.  At 11am exactly I heard the staff in the room.  They had come in to clean the room (without calling first) an hour before checkout time.

When I went out I saw how he had quietly and carefully wedge the door open already expecting that there was such a trap; showing that he had developed this skill over time and that he was aware that he was sneaking in instead of calling.

I was enraged!  I come from Texas where the law says that if someone did this at either my home OR A HOTEL that I would have the legal right to kill them.

I know that Myanmar law does not allow that and I respect Myanmar law; however they need to realize that they are authorized for foreign customers and they should try to give reasonable respect that when we are paying to sleep in a place that we have a right to privacy.

I cannot consider this hotel to be safe as you are not entitled to security of a safe space.

I have talked to Myanmar friends and this behavior is also not acceptable by their own culture.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Trip.com Member","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/local-reviews/AJMZ0QeCck1CfANpZm9bBk3PHtP97Kh9k25HZfvq9yAWlN3BaIyjSHUPEfWkhAJmuYiJsH-_6g=s120-c-br100","Rating":0,"Description":"Smokers room and unable to sleep in room, called the reception they offered air freshener when I had booked a non-smoking room. The staff isn't helpful; they can't smile, and some even have a bad attitude. They don't seem to care about the customers at all. The chair they placed outside the hotel is broken; I sat on it, and it broke on me. The staff and receptionist didn't even notice. When I told them the chair broke, they came and just put it back as it was before. I got some bruises, and they didn't even say sorry.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNsvAfIgy0-YEGlMAIYCLHXfohxuZrYzuyLvt7v&fid=0x0:0x1f5edf542c88a65b"],"When":"2023-10-18"},{"Name":"Trina Taylor","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocJc45quf8GKvNZR2kFNJotUX3LAUzZcwSnSi3Vd4XwsjfE2M_0=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"The room was clean, the staff was very friendly and helpful. We stayed here for four days, and their breakfast changed everyday which is what we really enjoyed trying new food everyday. The location  was really good. There are a lot of street food around this area.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Jason N","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/local-reviews/AJMZ0Qdx0CtChWdL4amzhVtedU6JgNzs3A9KzPS8K998c7-u-mDeTb-7WQwuTD-PPX6BcVA5wg=s120-c-br100","Rating":0,"Description":"I didn't have high hopes for this hotel, but the photos and rating seemed good.  I should have been more cautious and read the reviews more carefully.  First, there is no elevator.  My fault for not checking that, so no negative rating for this.  The hotel has 8 floors so you may have to climb 8 stories to your room. The biggest shock factor was how old and beat up the rooms were.  The website pictures look nice but are either photoshopped or so old that they no longer are accurate.  The walls are dirty and covered in the blood of many dead mosquitoes.  The bathrooms used to have white grout, but now are black with mildew.  -2 rating for horribly accurate pictures.  Second, the hotel does nothing for mosquito control.  I stayed in multiple hotels throughout Myanmar and every hotel was proactive at controlling the mosquitoes.  This place does nothing and the rooms were filled with them.  We got bit multiple times during the night.  -1 rating for mosquito control.  We got the entire floor (two rooms), and one of the rooms smelled of cigarette smoke.  -1 rating for that.  +1 rating as the staff seemed nice, the breakfast was decent, and location was good.  That adds up to a +2 rating.  I would not recommend this place at all.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Sarah R","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/local-reviews/AJMZ0QeFH6dzZjd_ZFLhXHZKibEzXEy8hWzFB4Qa7PutLe3CnO2G7yVfjd4VSabiCQwQYo5W-g=s120-c-br100","Rating":0,"Description":"Coming from Siem Reap it took my brain a little bit to adjust to a new economy! The first hotel I booked at $20 per night was an absolute dive. I got out of there as quickly as I could! Walked into Hotel Bond having checked it out online, yes it was a higher price, but worth every penny. The staff were so welcoming when I turned up at 8 in the morning, got me settled into a room and even invited me to have breakfast. The staff carried my suitcase up the stairs and even with the shared bathroom, i never saw the other guest sharing the bathroom so there was no conflict there. The bathroom was excellent with a rainforest shower and a smaller shower head. My suggestions here would be to get some bigger shampoo and shower gel bottles, the tiny individual ones are a waste of plastic and in this case space given that it is a shared bathroom. Putting some floor mats for the bathroom would also be a good idea, 2-3 so each room can have their own.||The room was small but very comfortable and clean.||The breakfast was decent and the daily noodle dish was always vegetable only which is just perfect!||My only other recommendation would be large water refills. Whilst having large water bottles as well as small is a big step above most hotels, I would prefer to use no plastic at all. When I asked the guy at the desk where I might refill my bottle, he said he didn't know and to maybe try a pagoda, when I walked out the door it was less than 30 seconds before I saw that there are water tanks on the street all over the place and these are for anyone to use! Hurrah! Still it would be great if the hotel included water refills in their breakfast room.","Images":null,"When":""}]

title: Hotel H Valley Yangon
address: 24 Shwe Gon Taing Street 3, Yangon
descriptions: Cosy rooms & suites in a laid-back hotel offering a bar, a restaurant & a cafe, plus free breakfast.
user_reviews:
[{"Name":"Ye Linn Aung","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVZoaCe4c9RPsb86zp6LF15u3dKGeMIQ9TEi8FCYnu80I2P2Nqfkg=s120-c-rp-mo-ba7-br100","Rating":3,"Description":"Modern Comfort in the Heart of Yangon

Looking for contemporary style and amenities in the center of historic Yangon? Look no further than the H Valley Hotel. This modern hotel boasts sleek rooms, first-rate service, and a prime location to experience all that Yangon offers.

From the moment I walked into the lobby, I was impressed by the chic, minimalist decor. Rooms follow the same aesthetic with floor-to-ceiling windows, plush white linens, and a muted gray and teal color scheme. Touches like rainfall showers, free Wi-Fi, and city views from my room made it an urban oasis. I loved starting mornings with the lavish breakfast buffet.

But what I appreciated most was the excellent service. The friendly staff went above and beyond, arranging tours, transportation, dining reservations, and airport transfers seamlessly. Their attention to detail embodies Asian hospitality.

For visitors who crave modern amenities without sacrificing an authentic cultural experience, H Valley is a perfect home base. This polished hotel lets you indulge in 21st-century comforts while exploring one of Asia’s most mesmerizing cities.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Mike E","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/local-reviews/AJMZ0Qf66pF81jsVXBxevYxxL5FsdlDsKAngAUpJVE-hAwai1rl8J0QnYqktKV3UGdpbmNlc_A=s120-c-br100","Rating":0,"Description":"Set on a side street, 10 minutes walk from Shwedagon Pagoda. Reception staff ordered a 'Grab' taxi for me.|Would definitely recommend this hotel and return here myself.|Great value for money","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"TJ N","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/local-reviews/AJMZ0QeCck1CfANpZm9bBk3PHtP97Kh9k25HZfvq9yAWlN3BaIyjSHUPEfWkhAJmuYiJsH-_6g=s120-c-br100","Rating":0,"Description":"The hotel is centrally located in a local vibes neighborhood within a walking distance to the Shwedagon pagoda. What truly sets the Grand Galaxy Hotel apart is the outstanding service. The staff members are not only professional but also warm and welcoming. They go out of their way to ensure that guests feel attended to and valued. Whether it was a request for room service or assistance with local recommendations, the staff was always ready to help with a smile.

Dining at the hotel was a highlight of my stay. The variety of culinary options catered to every taste, and the quality of the food was outstanding. The chefs clearly prioritize using fresh and high-quality ingredients, creating a memorable dining experience.

The hotel's amenities are top-notch with a well-equipped fitness center.

The Grand Galaxy Hotel's location is also worth mentioning. It's conveniently situated, allowing easy access to key attractions and making it a great base for both business and leisure travelers.
Overall, my experience at the Grand Galaxy Hotel was exceptional. I would highly recommend it to anyone looking for a blend of luxury, comfort, and outstanding service. I had a problem with their very slow Wifi.||The staffs were very helpful \u0026 friendly. Good buffet breakfast on the 6th floor. Many restaurants near were O.K. Reasonable price for hotel in Yangon.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Jozef D","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/local-reviews/AJMZ0Qdx0CtChWdL4amzhVtedU6JgNzs3A9KzPS8K998c7-u-mDeTb-7WQwuTD-PPX6BcVA5wg=s120-c-br100","Rating":0,"Description":"I stayed at M.G.M. hotel for the second time (first time was in June 2015). My stay now was from 4 to 14 December 2017. The reason I selected this hotel was on the first place because of the interesting location (at least for me). Yangon is gradually becoming a hellhole of traffic jams. However, taxis starting at M.G.M. hotel find easily their way as well to Pyay Road and the airport as to the city center. At the same time, the hotel is near to a number of green lanes where  one can still observe authentic Burmese daily life. As for the hotel itself, it's a place where you can feel at ease. The staff is friendly, polite and helpful. I knew from my previous stay that I should avoid sleeping in a room above the Karaoke bar on the second floor. I slept on the 8th floor, where at night it was quiet except for the barking of swerving groups of dogs. These dogs are very peaceful during the day but seemingly become aggressive when they form kind of gangs during the night. Breakfast at M.G.M. hotel is good and abundant. However, if you like the rice, noodles, vegetables, eggs, etc...  warm, rather enjoy them at 7 AM and not at 9 AM.  On the first floor there's a good Chinese restaurant, and around the hotel restaurants of all categories and prices abound. Just next door is the Japanese restaurant Doreen. There's foot massage available  just at the right side of the hotel and also at other places at walking distance. Walking briskly you can reach Scott Market and Sule Pagoda in the city center in less than half an hour. Guided by a Licensed Tour Guide (Than Than Htwe@Hannah), I needed more time, but I learned a lot about the history and heritage value of buildings in Chinatown and the Indian quarter. While working in my hotel room, I experienced that WIFI quality had much improved since 2015, but sometimes download speed was still too low.","Images":null,"When":""}]

[{"Name":"Vincent Wu (FlyingPorkbelly)","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWDIGHt7e5AsMQl8KQ9949cIXnfI8P56xutNR6F0nHk9kry2eiH4w=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Spent a week in room 988. awesome service and courteous attitudes from the staff. location is a bit far off from city but top ripper for businses trips for visiting nearby factories. excellent breakfast options which dont disappoint.

bar is a little dull with few people but awesome for someone wants to be quiet.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOG0gf2EP1MioZkUYBVrmHoTY6f6QQlYkwy-gTY&fid=0x0:0x3e371c6cd19fff83"],"When":"2024-5-23"},{"Name":"Kenneth Duan","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWIYaQoqDvyRFKa66rsi-1V0Kp-wSc9QKiqxxfrwLgcwmd5gnbO=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"My stay at the Riverview Hotel was a blend of highs and lows, resulting in a middling rating of three stars out of five. While the hotel boasted some commendable aspects, there were also notable areas that fell short of expectations.

Upon arrival, I was greeted by a courteous receptionist who efficiently checked me in. The lobby exuded a sophisticated ambiance with its modern decor and comfortable seating areas. However, the check-in process felt slightly disorganized, with a longer wait time than anticipated.

Entering my room, I was initially impressed by its cleanliness and spacious layout. The bed was comfortable, and the linens appeared fresh. However, upon closer inspection, I noticed some signs of wear and tear, such as scuff marks on the furniture and a few stains on the carpet. Additionally, the room lacked certain amenities that are becoming standard in many hotels, such as a coffee maker and mini-fridge.

The bathroom, while adequately sized, had outdated fixtures and could benefit from a renovation. The water pressure in the shower was inconsistent, alternating between strong bursts and weak dribbles. Furthermore, the toiletries provided were of subpar quality, failing to meet the standard expected from a hotel of this caliber.

One of the highlights of my stay was the hotel's dining options. The breakfast buffet offered a variety of delicious dishes, ranging from traditional favorites to international selections. The restaurant staff were attentive and accommodating, ensuring a pleasant dining experience. However, the prices were on the higher side, and I felt that the value for money could have been better.

The hotel's amenities left much to be desired. While there was a fitness center available, it was small and poorly equipped. Additionally, the pool area was underwhelming, with limited seating and a lack of ambiance. It seemed as though these facilities were an afterthought rather than a focal point of the hotel's offerings.

In terms of location, the Riverview Hotel was conveniently situated near several attractions and transportation options. However, the surrounding area was noisy, especially at night, which detracted from the overall tranquility of the stay. Furthermore, parking was limited and expensive, adding an extra inconvenience for guests with vehicles.

On the service front, the staff were generally friendly and helpful, although there were instances where communication was lacking. For example, requests made to the front desk were sometimes forgotten or took longer than expected to fulfill. Additionally, housekeeping could be inconsistent, with some days seeing thorough cleanings while others left much to be desired.

Overall, my experience at the Riverview Hotel was a mixed bag. While there were aspects to appreciate, such as the dining options and cleanliness of the rooms, there were also notable shortcomings, including outdated facilities and inconsistent service. With some improvements in these areas, the hotel has the potential to elevate its rating and provide a more satisfying experience for guests.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Ko Kyaw","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXk3SOvIliN7feYgaUVVkur6fMkjVbC2q0sbZDoKcRXWKV7QYwoCw=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"Very well decorated.
